data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3611856\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 08, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104afm1665702915228.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/afm1665702915228.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/afm1665702915228.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"afm1665702915228\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Uniface Reference\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"afm1665702915228__uniface_reference_208741\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Uniface Reference collection assembles all reference documentation in one place\n      for easy access, including ProcScript language instructions, API calls, trigger and widget\n      descriptions, messages, settings, and so on.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"afm1665702915228__p_d69326e1_d69327e1_d69328e1\">For information on the syntax used in reference documentation, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xuk1665702784874.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xuk1665702784874.html\" title=\"The Uniface documentation employs a number of conventions for documenting the syntax and user interface of Uniface products.\">Documentation Conventions</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"afm1665702915228__topic_d45372e1_d45373e1_d45374e1_d45375e1_d45376e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d915403e63\">\n Development Objects\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31541e1_d31542e1_d31543e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dbs1665702541439.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dbs1665702541439.html\" title=\"Uniface Development Objects are data types that define the characteristics and properties that different application definitions. There are many types of Development Object, but they are all specializations of the basic Uniface Development Object.\">Development Objects Reference</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31544e1_d31545e1_d31546e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ksl1665702915298.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ksl1665702915298.html\" title=\"Every development object has properties which can be viewed and edited in the Properties Inspector.\">Development Object Properties</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31547e1_d31548e1_d31549e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pdm1665702915368.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pdm1665702915368.html\" title=\"When defining fields, you can specify the field interface, syntax, and layout definitions, either directly or in a template.\">Field Definitions</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"afm1665702915228__topic_d45377e1_d45378e1_d45379e1_d45380e1_d45381e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d915403e102\">\n Widgets\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31550e1_d31551e1_d31552e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lov1718340866615.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lov1718340866615.html\" title=\"Widgets in Form components determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities in components running on Windows.\">Widget Reference: Forms and Reports</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31553e1_d31554e1_d31555e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qxh1718771608803.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qxh1718771608803.html\" title=\"Widgets in dynamic server pages (DSPs) determine the appearance and behavior of fields, labels, occurrences, and entities displayed in the client browser.\">Widget Reference: Dynamic Server Pages</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31556e1_d31557e1_d31558e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xcx1665703126648.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xcx1665703126648.html\" title=\"Uniface provides a set of HTML controls for use in static server pages (USPs).\">Widget Reference: Static Server Pages</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31559e1_d31560e1_d31561e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iyz1665703128007.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iyz1665703128007.html\" title=\"Uniface-specific XHTML elements are used in the layout of static server pages (USPs). They act as placeholders for entities, occurrences, fields, and labels and provide processing instructions for generating the runtime XHTML. At run time, these tags are replaced by XHTML code and controls containing the actual data.\">XHTML Elements for Static Server Pages</a></li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"afm1665702915228__topic_d45382e1_d45383e1_d45384e1_d45385e1_d45386e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d915403e147\">\n Script Modules\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31562e1_d31563e1_d31564e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uug1665702660378.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uug1665702660378.html\" title=\"System triggers are script modules that are synchronously executed in response to system events that are initiated by commands. System trigger names are predetermined and case-insensitive.\">Triggers: System</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31565e1_d31566e1_d31567e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gao1665702660518.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gao1665702660518.html\" title=\"Interactive triggers are script modules that are executed in response to events associated with a specific object in a user interface component. They can be fired as a result of user actions, such as clicking a widget or changing its value. Alternatively, some triggers can be invoked by their corresponding macro or the callfieldtrigger ProcScript command.\">Triggers: Interactive</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31568e1_d31569e1_d31570e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ord1665702915442.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ord1665702915442.html\">Triggers: Web</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31571e1_d31572e1_d31573e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"orp1665702625432.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/orp1665702625432.html\" title=\"Predefined operations are operations and triggers that Uniface executes in specific circumstances. If declared, these ProcScript modules are exposed in the component signature.\">Predefined Operations</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31574e1_d31575e1_d31576e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jhx1665702915512.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jhx1665702915512.html\" title=\"Code containers are properties of development objects that hold constant declarations and script modules.\">Containers</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"afm1665702915228__topic_d45387e1_d45388e1_d45389e1_d45390e1_d45391e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d915403e212\">\n ProcScript\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31577e1_d31578e1_d31579e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eqt1665702682684.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eqt1665702682684.html\" title=\"Data types define the characteristics of the data and determine how Uniface handles the data during processing and storage. They are specified for parameters, variables, and return values in ProcScript, as well as for fields, global variables, and component variables.\">ProcScript: Data Types</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31580e1_d31581e1_d31582e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tpi1665702624640.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tpi1665702624640.html\" title=\"The Uniface ProcScript language consists of a series of ProcScript statements that cause Uniface to perform specified actions, such as running a form, retrieving data, locking an occurrence, calling another ProcScript module, and so on.\">ProcScript: Statements</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31583e1_d31584e1_d31585e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rfg1665702624715.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rfg1665702624715.html\" title=\"Refer to the topics under this section to understand functions related to ProcScript.\">ProcScript: Functions</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31586e1_d31587e1_d31588e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mlc1665702620662.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mlc1665702620662.html\" title=\"Precompiler directives and Uniface constants enable you to produce generalized, reusable ProcScript. They allow you to determine the exact composition of the ProcScript that will be compiled.\">ProcScript: Precompiler Directives and Uniface Constants</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31589e1_d31590e1_d31591e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kxu1665702565358.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kxu1665702565358.html\" title=\"Struct functions enable you to get information about a Struct (such as the number of members it has), get or set Struct annotations, or perform actions such as inserting and moving Struct members. Syntactically, they are treated as Struct members and are accessed using the de-reference operator (-&gt;). However, they are not part of the Struct member list and they do not have an index.\">ProcScript: Struct Functions</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"afm1665702915228__topic_d45392e1_d45393e1_d45394e1_d45395e1_d45396e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d915403e274\">\n APIs\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31592e1_d31593e1_d31594e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"evi1665702596474.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/evi1665702596474.html\" title=\"Unless otherwise indicated, all 3GL functions are available on all platforms.\">APIs: 3GL Functions</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31595e1_d31596e1_d31597e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fpf1665702915593.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fpf1665702915593.html\" title=\"Use the Database Connector Interface as an API for building custom database connectors.\">APIs: Database Connector Interface</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31598e1_d31599e1_d31600e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"owl1665702532596.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/owl1665702532596.html\" title=\"The Uniface JavaScript API is a collection of object-oriented programming interfaces that can be used in dynamic server pages (DSPs) to manipulate Uniface data objects in the browser, without round-trip processing to the server.\">APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31601e1_d31602e1_d31603e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ebt1665702919180.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ebt1665702919180.html\" title=\"Java applications call in to the operations of a Uniface component via the URB. Uniface generates Java classes and methods based on the component’s signature.\">APIs: Java Call-In Classes and Methods</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31604e1_d31605e1_d31606e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aqt1665702677943.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqt1665702677943.html\" title=\"Uniface provides an API for creating custom client/server and SMTP and POP security drivers. The API include files for the C compiler and libraries are provided in the Uniface/3gl directory.\">APIs: Security Driver</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31607e1_d31608e1_d31609e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mdc1665702668356.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mdc1665702668356.html\" title=\"The session management API provides an interface to the Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) that enables you to change and control the HTTP session. You can invalidate the current session, or create a new session with (or without) the same state information and session attributes.\">APIs: Session Management</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31610e1_d31611e1_d31612e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrr1675954670899.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrr1675954670899.html\" title=\"Uniface component APIs are internal Uniface components that enable users to interact with many third-party applications and standards and to access public Uniface internal data and functionality. They are activated, as any normal component, use the activate ProcScript command to call their operations.\">APIs: Uniface Components</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"afm1665702915228__topic_d45397e1_d45398e1_d45399e1_d45400e1_d45401e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d915403e363\">\n Configuration Settings\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31613e1_d31614e1_d31615e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eao1665702739907.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eao1665702739907.html\" title=\"Assignment files contain assignments and settings that define the environment of a Uniface application. Assignments tell Uniface where to find the resources, connectors, servers and external components that the application needs, and how to connect to them. Assignment settings define other aspects of the application behavior.\">Configuration Settings: Assignment</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31616e1_d31617e1_d31618e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gyp1665702675022.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gyp1665702675022.html\" title=\"Initialization settings are used to configure the application on a specific platform.\">Configuration Settings: Initialization</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31619e1_d31620e1_d31621e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xvg1665702743974.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xvg1665702743974.html\" title=\"Uniface servlets run in the environment of the web application. Settings for the Uniface servlets, the WRD and SRD, are stored in the web.xml file, which is the configuration file of the web application.\">Configuration Settings: Uniface Servlet</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"afm1665702915228__topic_d45402e1_d45403e1_d45404e1_d45405e1_d45406e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d915403e405\">\n Messages\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31622e1_d31623e1_d31624e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nqh1665702549702.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nqh1665702549702.html\" title=\"Most of the messages that display in the message frame are determined by the I/O message level. The I/O message is a number that is determined by adding up the codes of the applicable message types.\">I/O Message Levels</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31625e1_d31626e1_d31627e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"spb1665702919328.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/spb1665702919328.html\" title=\"Database connector requests are recognized by every Uniface DBMS connector. Each request is identified by an alphabetic character, such as O for Open or S for Select. You need to know these requests and the modes that some of them use, when analyzing I/O messages in the message frame.\">Database Connector Requests</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31628e1_d31629e1_d31630e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"scc1665702919621.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/scc1665702919621.html\" title=\"Understand the error, warning, or information messages that might display for the compiler.\">Compiler Messages</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31631e1_d31632e1_d31633e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nmp1665702736587.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nmp1665702736587.html\" title=\"If SQL generation fails, Uniface reports a warning or error.\">SQL Generation Messages</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31634e1_d31635e1_d31636e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"glj1665702919701.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/glj1665702919701.html\" title=\"Understand how Uniface messages are used (for example, message severity levels, message numbering scheme, or how message text is displayed).\">Uniface Messages</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31637e1_d31638e1_d31639e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wir1665702744693.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wir1665702744693.html\" title=\"During import, migration, and compilation, Uniface generates messages about the success or failure of the migration, and the issues encountered.\">Import and Migration Messages</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"afm1665702915228__topic_d45407e1_d45408e1_d45409e1_d45410e1_d45411e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d915403e475\">Rocket® Uniface </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31640e1_d31641e1_d31642e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pqr1665702919772.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pqr1665702919772.html\" title=\"Uniface provides many tools and servers for developing, integrating, deploying, and running complex, component-based applications. Some tools are available in the Uniface IDE, others are standalone utilities. Many utilities are available from the command line, enabling them to be used in batch mode.\">Uniface Tools</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31643e1_d31644e1_d31645e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ija1665702745041.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ija1665702745041.html\" title=\"Command line switches can be used with Uniface executables to specify configuration files, run utilities, supply parameters, apply operating constraints, and otherwise qualify the session. They remain in effect for the duration of that application session.\">Command Line Switches Reference</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31646e1_d31647e1_d31648e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sjo1665702919851.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sjo1665702919851.html\" title=\"During installation, a large number of files and executables are installed. Some of the most important are described in the topics in this section.\">Uniface Files and Executables</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31649e1_d31650e1_d31651e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yoi1665702919920.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yoi1665702919920.html\" title=\"Uniface delivers a set of glyphs for use in its own tools and editors. New glyphs are added in each new version of Uniface, sometimes replacing older glyphs, sometimes as additions.\">Uniface Glyphs</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31652e1_d31653e1_d31654e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cwu1665702919990.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cwu1665702919990.html\" title=\"The maximum values that occur throughout Uniface are inherent limits that you need to consider as you develop applications. Your DBMS or operating system may impose further restrictions of its own.\">Uniface Maximums</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31655e1_d31656e1_d31657e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eew1665702619155.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eew1665702619155.html\" title=\"The name of a development object is its unique identifier. When naming development objects, use the allowed syntax for the object name. Avoid using words that are reserved for use within Uniface and your own environment, including the operating system and database.\">Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31658e1_d31659e1_d31660e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujc1665702619229.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujc1665702619229.html\" title=\"Reserved words are terms that cannot be used to name your Rocket Uniface objects.\">Uniface Reserved Words</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31661e1_d31662e1_d31663e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zcc1665702920067.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zcc1665702920067.html\" title=\"A retrieve profile is used to control the scope of the data to be retrieved from the database. It consists of one or more values for one or more fields in an entity, often containing profile characters. In essence, a retrieve profile is a search query.\">Retrieve Profile Characters</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"afm1665702915228__topic_d45412e1_d45413e1_d45414e1_d45415e1_d45416e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d915403e569\">\n XML\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"afm1665702915228__li_d31664e1_d31665e1_d31666e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bwz1665702567697.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bwz1665702567697.html\" title=\"Uniface enables you to use and manipulate data in a variety of ways, including Structs, Uniface XML streams, and component-based APIs, UXMLREADER and UXMLWRITER .\">Uniface XML Constructs</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3611856\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3611856\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Reference Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 08, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Reference The Uniface Reference collection assembles all reference documentation in one place for easy access, including ProcScript language instructions, API calls, trigger and widget descriptions, messages, settings, and so on. For information on the syntax used in reference documentation, see Documentation Conventions . Development Objects Development Objects Reference Development Object Properties Field Definitions Widgets Widget Reference: Forms and Reports Widget Reference: Dynamic Server Pages Widget Reference: Static Server Pages XHTML Elements for Static Server Pages Script Modules Triggers: System Triggers: Interactive Triggers: Web Predefined Operations Containers ProcScript ProcScript: Data Types ProcScript: Statements ProcScript: Functions ProcScript: Precompiler Directives and Uniface Constants ProcScript: Struct Functions APIs APIs: 3GL Functions APIs: Database Connector Interface APIs: DSP Client-Side JavaScript APIs: Java Call-In Classes and Methods APIs: Security Driver APIs: Session Management APIs: Uniface Components Configuration Settings Configuration Settings: Assignment Configuration Settings: Initialization Configuration Settings: Uniface Servlet Messages I/O Message Levels Database Connector Requests Compiler Messages SQL Generation Messages Uniface Messages Import and Migration Messages Rocket® Uniface Uniface Tools Command Line Switches Reference Uniface Files and Executables Uniface Glyphs Uniface Maximums Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects Uniface Reserved Words Retrieve Profile Characters XML Uniface XML Constructs Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}